    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Follow One's Nose</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sara Nicoll letter on importance of good food aromas in restaurants (May 10 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your article ''What's a Nose to Do? Nothing'' (May 10) was interesting in that it pointed out the difference between the European and American attitude toward restaurant aromatic cleansing. I just returned from Venice, where the concierge of our hotel, when asked for a recommendation to a restaurant, pointed to his nose and said, ''Follow your nose.'' We did. And he was right. We didn't need any other guide.</p>
        <p>SARA NICOLL  New York</p>
      </block>
